# Documentation & adjustability comments

Every file in this project must be easy to open later and change safely. Prefer short, plain language over long essays.

## Required docs

- **Module / file**: one-line summary at the top (what it is for).
- **Public class / function / view**: short docstring — purpose, important inputs, what it returns or renders, and any rule that must stay true when editing.
- **Templates**: a short HTML comment at the top naming the page/partial and which admin/CMS fields feed it (when relevant).
- **CSS sections**: a short comment before each major block (header, booking slots, dashboard, etc.).
- **JS**: one-line purpose at the top; comment non-obvious selectors or behavior.

## Comments that help editing

- Mark **tunable values** (hours, prices defaults, colors, slot length, copy keys) with a short note, e.g. `# Adjust: default slot length for new weekly rules`.
- Explain **why** for non-obvious branches, not what the next line literally does.
- Point to the **place to change** related behavior (admin model, form field, CSS variable, URL name).
- Do not narrate obvious code (`# increment i`) or leave stale comments.

